20every%20year%20since%202020.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThese%C2%A0%26quot%3BBig%20Whale%26quot%3B%C2%A0subs%20are%20expected%20to%20hunt%20Chinese%20warships%20should%20a%20war%20break%20out.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETheir%20advanced%20capabilities%20and%20stealth%20make%20them%20prime%20candidates%20for%20ambushes%20on%20Chinese%20warships.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20Kawasaki%20Heavy%20Industries%20launched%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20newest%20submarine%20in%20a%20ceremony%20at%20its%20shipyard%20in%20Kobe%2C%20Japan.%20Named%2C%20JS%20Raigei%20(%E2%80%9CThunder%20Whale%E2%80%9D%20in%20Japanese)%2C%20the%20diesel-electric%20attack%20sub%20is%20the%20fourth%20boat%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mod.go.jp%2Fmsdf%2Fequipment%2Fships%2Fss%2Ftaigei%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETaigei-class%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20translates%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbig%20whale.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20launch%20comes%20almost%20exactly%20one%20year%20after%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20third%20Taigei-class%20sub%2C%20JS%20Jingei%20(or%20%E2%80%9CSwift%20Whale%E2%80%9D).%20With%20a%20building%20time%20of%20about%20two%20years%20each%2C%20Japan%20has%20launched%20a%20new%20Taigei-class%20sub%20every%20year%20since%202020.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20quick%20timetable%20demonstrates%20more%20than%20the%20excellent%20turnaround%20time%20of%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20major%20shipbuilders%3B%20it%20also%20demonstrates%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20resolve%20to%20modernize%20its%20submarine%20fleet%20with%20a%20new%20class%20of%20diesel-electric%20submarine%20regarded%20as%20one%20of%20the%20best%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeaturing%20a%20host%20of%20new%20technologies%20and%20innovations%2C%20Taigei-class%20subs%20were%20designed%20in%20large%20part%20to%20defend%20from%20the%20very%20real%20and%20growing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.usni.org%2F2024%2F02%2F01%2Freport-to-congress-on-chinese-naval-modernization-20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethreat%20posed%20by%20China%E2%80%99s%20navy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20are%20expected%20to%20play%20an%20essential%20role%20in%20hunting%20Chinese%20warships%20should%20a%20war%20break%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENew%20threats%2C%20advanced%20subs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJapan%E2%80%99s%20submarine%20prowess%20is%20the%20result%20of%20a%20large%20industrial%20base%20and%20a%20wealth%20of%20experience%20building%20and%20operating%20submarines%20for%20over%20a%20century.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJapan%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naval-technology.com%2Fprojects%2Fsssoryuclasssubmarin%2F%3Fcf-view%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ES%C5%8Dry%C5%AB-class%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20pronounced%20%E2%80%9Csoar-yuu%2C%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20especially%20lauded%20for%20its%20effectiveness%20and%20advanced%20capabilities%2C%20including%20being%20one%20of%20the%20first%20frontline%20submarine%20classes%20to%20be%20equipped%20with%20air-independent%20propulsion%20(AIP)%20technology%2C%20which%20allows%20diesel-electric%20boats%20to%20operate%20underwater%20for%20longer%20periods.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20technological%20sophistication%20of%20their%20submarines%2C%20combined%20with%20the%20might%20of%20allied%20US%20Navy%20nuclear-powered%20attack%20subs%2C%20enabled%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20navy%2C%20known%20officially%20as%20the%20Japan%20Maritime%20Self-Defense%20Force%20(JMSDF)%2C%20to%20field%20a%20small%20sub%20fleet%20compared%20to%20its%20neighbors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20the%20years%20immediately%20after%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20with%20the%20threat%20from%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20virtually%20vanishing%20overnight%20and%20the%20one%20from%20Russia%20appearing%20significantly%20degraded%20compared%20to%20its%20forebear%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20submarine%20fleet%2C%20though%20large%2C%20was%20still%20mostly%20regarded%20as%20generations%20behind%20in%20terms%20of%20capability%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20technological%20gap.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20however%2C%20that%20gap%20has%20closed%20dramatically.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20current%20sub%20fleet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iiss.org%2Fen%2Fpublications%2Fthe-military-balance%2Fthe-military-balance-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enumbering%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20some%2059%20boats%2C%20includes%20approximately%2010%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naval-technology.com%2Fprojects%2Fkilo%2F%3Fcf-view%26cf-closed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eimproved%20Kilo-class%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2012%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naval-technology.com%2Fprojects%2Fsongclassubmarine%2F%3Fcf-view%26cf-closed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EType%20039-class%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%2021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.usni.org%2F2015%2F08%2F31%2Fessay-inside-the-design-of-chinas-yuan-class-submarine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EType%20039A-class%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20diesel-electric%20attack%20subs.%20The%20force%20also%20includes%20six%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naval-technology.com%2Fprojects%2Fshang-class-nuclear-powered-attack-submarines-china%2F%3Fcf-view%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EType%20093%2F093A%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20nuclear-propelled%20attack%20submarines%20and%20six%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fglimpse-chinese-ballistic-missile-submarines%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EType-094%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20nuclear-powered%20ballistic%20missile%20submarines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20models%20are%20equipped%20with%20modern%20systems%20and%20weaponry%2C%20and%20have%20modern%20capabilities.%20The%20Yuan-class%20boats%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20are%20outfitted%20with%20AIP%20technology%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navalnews.com%2Fnaval-news%2F2023%2F11%2Fchinese-submarine-is-first-to-exploit-new-stealth-technology%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eappear%20to%20be%20getting%20upgrades%20to%20make%20them%20stealthier%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20China%20has%20become%20increasingly%20assertive%20with%20its%20naval%20forces%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.japantimes.co.jp%2Fnews%2F2023%2F12%2F30%2Fjapan%2Fchina-daily-senkakus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Earound%20the%20Senkaku%20Islands%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20Beijing%20claims%20but%20Japan%20maintains%20sovereignty%20over.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20Japan%20needs%20to%20both%20increase%20the%20size%20of%20its%20submarine%20fleet%2C%20and%20equip%20each%20sub%20with%20advanced%20technologies%20to%20achieve%20a%20qualitative%20advantage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223680%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Japan%20is%20building%20a%20larger%20submarine%20fleet%20but%20it%20is%20still%20only%20about%20a%20third%20the%20size%20of%20China's.%20This%20image%20shows%20the%20Soryu-class%20submarine%20Kokuryu.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c5123343bb77284ba4fbc3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJapan%20is%20building%20a%20larger%20submarine%20fleet%20but%20it%20is%20still%20only%20about%20a%20third%20the%20size%20of%20China's.%20This%20image%20shows%20the%20S%C5%8Dry%C5%AB-class%20submarine%20Kokuryu.%3Cp%3EJapan%20Maritime%20Self-Defense%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Big%20Whale%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20a%20year%20after%20the%20commissioning%20of%20the%20first%20S%C5%8Dry%C5%AB-class%20sub%2C%20Japan%20unveiled%20plans%20to%20increase%20its%20submarine%20fleet%20from%2016%20to%2022%20boats.%20It%20also%20continued%20to%20pursue%20new%20technologies%20it%20had%20started%20researching%20in%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20the%202000s.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20those%20technologies%20was%20lithium-ion%20(Li-ion)%20batteries.%20Much%20more%20efficient%20than%20standard%20lead-acid%20batteries%2C%20Li-ion%20batteries%20maintain%20a%20larger%20voltage%20potential%20as%20they%20discharge%20energy.%20They%20are%20also%20generally%20more%20energy%20dense%20and%20can%20be%20capable%20of%20storing%20twice%20as%20much%20energy%20as%20lead-acid%20batteries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20submarines%2C%20this%20means%20faster%20accelerations%20and%20top%20speeds%2C%20more%20time%20underwater%2C%20less%20maintenance%2C%20faster%20recharge%20times%2C%20lower%20noise%20levels%2C%20and%20better%20overall%20performance.%20Li-ion%20batteries%20also%20negate%20the%20need%20for%20AIP%2C%20since%20they%20are%20more%20efficient%20and%20already%20store%20so%20much%20energy.%C2%A0Submarines%20need%20burst%20speeds%20to%20evade%20depth%20charges%20and%20homing%20torpedoes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20other%20navies%20have%20been%20reluctant%20to%20adopt%20Li-ion%20batteries%20for%20submarines%20because%20of%20the%20risks%20of%20them%20malfunctioning%20and%20starting%20fires%2C%20Japan%20became%20the%20first%20(and%20so%20far%20only)%20country%20to%20integrate%20the%20technology%20into%20submarines%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-and-china-japan-launches-sub-with-lithium-ion-battery-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecommissioning%20of%20the%20final%20two%20S%C5%8Dry%C5%AB-class%20subs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20JS%20%C5%8Cry%C5%AB%2C%20and%20JS%20T%C5%8Dry%C5%AB.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Japan%20launched%20JS%20Taigei%2C%20the%20lead%20boat%20of%20its%20class%20and%20the%20first%20submarine%20designed%20from%20the%20outset%20to%20carry%20Li-ion%20batteries.%20Commissioned%20in%202022%2C%20it%20is%20similar%20in%20appearance%20to%20the%20S%C5%8Dry%C5%AB-class%2C%20but%20is%20slightly%20larger%2C%20measuring%20275%20ft%20long%20and%2030%20ft%20wide%2C%20with%20a%20surface%20displacement%20of%20approximately%203%2C000%20tons.%20A%20US%20Navy%20Los%20Angeles%20class%20attack%20sub%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20is%20about%2090%20feet%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20S%C5%8Dry%C5%AB-class%2C%20it%20is%20built%20with%20an%20X-shaped%20rudder%20for%20enhanced%20propulsion%20performance%20and%20operates%20the%20same%20countermeasure%20system.%20It%20is%20also%20equipped%20with%20the%20same%20ZPS-6F%20surface%2Flow-level%20air%20search%20radar%2C%20carries%20the%20same%20towed%20array%20sonar%2C%20and%20has%20an%20optronic%20mast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Taigei-class%20also%20has%20new%20systems%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20Li-ion%20batteries%2C%20including%20a%20new%20snorkel%20system%2C%20a%20new%20sonar%20system%20based%20on%20fiber-optic%20array%20technology%2C%20a%20new%20combat%20management%20system%20that%20gathers%20data%20from%20all%20sensors%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twz.com%2F31708%2Fveteran-sonarman-explains-why-pump-jets-are-superior-to-props-on-modern-submarines%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epump-jet%20propulsor%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20crew%20of%2070%2C%20the%20Taigei-class%20is%20also%20built%20with%20a%20female-only%20section%20in%20the%20crew%20compartment%20for%20six%20female%20submariners-%20the%20first%20such%20accommodation%20in%20a%20Japanese%20submarine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20subs%20have%20six%20torpedo%20tubes%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweaponsystems.net%2Fsystem%2F420-Type%2B89%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EType%2089%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Type%2018%20torpedoes%2C%20and%20are%20capable%20of%20launching%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmissilethreat.csis.org%2Fmissile%2Fharpoon%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUGM-84%20Harpoon%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20anti-ship%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20central%20role%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESubmarines%20have%20long%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usni.org%2Fmagazines%2Fproceedings%2F2023