%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foff-grid-lifestyle-is-not-for-everyone-and-thats-ok-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eentirely%20off%20the%20grid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20300-square-foot%20home%20that%20we%20built%20from%20straw%20bales%20and%20cob%2C%20a%20natural%20building%20material%20made%20from%20soil%2C%20water%2C%20and%20other%20organic%20matter.%20We%20rely%20on%20solar%20power%20for%20electricity%20and%20rain%20collection%20for%20water%2C%20and%20we%20use%20a%20drop%20toilet%20to%20create%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhumanurehandbook.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehumanure%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20compost%20made%20from%20human%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20left%20the%20conventional%20world%20behind.%20But%20along%20the%20way%20we've%20created%20a%20much%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-live-luxuriously-for-cheap-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20luxurious%20and%20free%20lifestyle%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20one%20we%20were%20living%20in%20suburbia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20started%20trying%20to%20live%20more%20consciously%20when%20the%20kids%20were%20young%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20journey%20started%20in%20an%20unlikely%20place%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-nightmare-netflix-true-crime-documentaries-watch-next-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetflix%20documentaries%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20kids%20are%20now%2011%20and%2013%2C%20but%20when%20they%20were%20younger%20I%20started%20learning%20from%20documentaries%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20chemicals%20and%20plastics.%20I%20started%20by%20making%20small%20changes%20within%20our%20traditional%20life%20%E2%80%94%20removing%20plastics%2C%20then%20cleaning%20with%20homemade%20solutions%20like%20vinegar%20and%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20while%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20there%20was%20only%20so%20far%20I%20could%20take%20that%20while%20living%20in%20a%20traditional%20setting.%20Casey%20and%20I%20felt%20the%20only%20way%20to%20really%20live%20by%20our%20values%20was%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-renovation-tips-diy-building-your-dream-home-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20a%20house%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20didn't%20feel%20insurmountable%2C%20so%20we%20started%20researching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20traveled%20the%20country%20and%20settled%20in%20North%20Carolina%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20fairly%20liberal.%20During%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectoral-college-donald-trump-president-official-2016-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%202016%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20lots%20of%20people%20vowed%20to%20change%20their%20lives%20if%20Trump%20was%20elected.%20We%20actually%20followed%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-zones-nicoya-costa-rica-whole-food-calcium-exercise-rest-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emove%20to%20Costa%20Rica%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20learn%20to%20live%20off%20the%20grid.%20But%20when%20we%20arrived%20there%2C%20we%20quickly%20realized%20that%20many%20of%20the%20expats%20who%20were%20living%20that%20lifestyle%20had%20imperialist%20attitudes.%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20physically%20healthier%20by%20living%20off%20the%20grid%2C%20but%20not%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20our%20morals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20returned%20to%20the%20US%20and%20spent%20four%20months%20traveling%20through%2038%20states%2C%20looking%20for%20a%20space%20that%20felt%20like%20home.%20We%20wanted%20somewhere%20warm%20enough%20to%20farm%2C%20with%20plentiful%20water%2C%20permissive%20building%20codes%2C%20and%20lots%20of%20space.%20We%20ended%20up%20with%2016%20acres%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20about%20an%20hour%20outside%20Winston-Salem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe're%20off%20the%20grid%20but%20use%20our%20neighbors%20and%20community%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20purchasing%20our%20land%2C%20we%20started%20to%20build.%20Our%20home%20consists%20of%20two%2012-foot-by-12-foot%20structures.%20One%20is%20the%20kitchen%2C%20and%20one%20is%20the%20bedroom%2C%20where%20Casey%20and%20I%20sleep%20on%20the%20floor%20level%20and%20the%20kids%20bunk%20above%20us.%20The%20two%20structures%20are%20connected%20by%20our%20greenhouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22House%20made%20with%20natural%20elements%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c159f57a3d27148877e3e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221122%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20family's%20house%20is%20made%20of%20natural%20elements%2C%20and%20they%20collect%20water%20from%20the%20roof.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20source%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20teach%20adult%20education%20part%20time%2C%20while%20Casey%20picks%20up%20occasional%20substituting%20jobs.%20We%20don't%20have%20many%20of%20the%20bills%20conventional%20families%20do.%20We%20use%20solar%20panels%20to%20power%20our%20fridge%20and%20charge%20our%20computers%2C%20phones%2C%20and%20e-readers.%20We%20collect%20our%20water%20from%20the%20roof%20and%20pump%20it%20using%20an%20old-fashioned%20hand%20crank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%20we%20hope%20to%20grow%20all%20our%20own%20food%2C%20but%20we're%20nowhere%20near%20that%20yet.%20We%20buy%20from%20the%20local%20farmers%20market%20and%20order%20a%20few%20things%2C%20like%20coconut%20milk%20and%20cassava%20flour%2C%20on%20Amazon%20%E2%80%94%20though%20we're%20trying%20to%20cut%20that%20out.%20When%20possible%2C%20we%20barter%20for%20what%20we%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOur%20days%20have%20an%20easy%20pace%20but%20lots%20of%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20days%20are%20slow.%20Everything%20we%20do%20is%20driven%20by%20either%20a%20want%20or%20a%20need.%20We%20don't%20do%20anything%20just%20because%20we%20%26quot%3Bshould.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20we%20sleep%20in%2C%20and%20everyone%