edia%20bodies%20expressed%20consternation%20over%20the%20upcoming%20law.%20Journalist%20bodies%20%E2%80%93%20The%20National%20Alliance%20of%20Journalists%20(NAJ)%2C%20the%20Delhi%20Union%20of%20Journalists%20(DUJ)%2C%20and%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20Working%20Journalists%20Federation%20(APWJF)%20join%20the%20Network%20of%20Women%20in%20Media%20India%2C%20(NWMI)%20and%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20and%20others%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fgateway-to-censorship-journalist-bodies-express-concern-over-proposed-broadcasting-services-bill%5C%22%3Ehave%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20reservations%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20proposed%20law.%20They%20describe%20it%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgateway%20to%20censorship%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20joint%20statement%20the%20NAJ%2C%20DUJ%2C%20and%20APWJF%20say%20that%20this%20proposed%20Bill%20is%20a%20step%20further%20%E2%80%9Cto%20expanding%20a%20new%20era%20of%20undeclared%20censorship%E2%80%9D%20and%20increasing%20government%20control%20over%20all%20types%20of%20media%20from%20TV%20channels%2C%20to%20films%2C%20and%20platforms%20like%20Netflix%20and%20Prime%20Video%2C%20YouTube%2C%20radio%2C%20even%20Instagram%20and%20other%20social%20media%20platforms%20as%20well%20as%20news%20websites%20and%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20(EGI)%20had%20written%20to%20Union%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20minister%20Anurag%20Thakur%20calling%20the%20draft%20of%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fvague-and-excessively-intrusive-editors-guild-of-india-to-centre-on-broadcast-services-bill%5C%22%3Evague%20and%20excessively%20intrusive%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20The%20EGI%2C%20whose%20mandate%20is%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20to%20raise%20standards%20of%20editorial%20leadership%E2%80%9D%20of%20news%20media%20outlets%2C%20had%20told%20the%20minister%20that%20the%20new%20Bill%20will%20prove%20%E2%80%9Cadverse%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20freedom%20of%20the%20press%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcontrol-all-or-delete-the-draft-broadcast-bill-is-a-blueprint-for-censorship%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20that%20%E2%80%9Cas%20a%C2%A0charter%20for%20censorship%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmib.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FPublic%2520Notice_0.pdf%5C%22%3Ethe%20Broadcasting%20Services%20(Regulation)%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Broadcast%20Bill)%20drafted%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20(MIB)%20is%20a%20remarkable%20instrument%E2%80%A6%20this%20is%20an%20omnibus%20set%20of%20rules%20aimed%20at%20shutting%20down%20any%20news%20or%20views%20even%20mildly%20not%20in%20the%20service%20of%20those%20who%20happen%20to%20be%20in%20government%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707551036000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F23203159%2FScreen-Shot-2020-10-23-at-8.31.43-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-tells-centre-to-expedite-passage-of-controversial-broadcasting-services-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%20on%20communication%20and%20information%20technology%20said%20it%20would%20like%20to%20'engage%20in%20constructive%20discussions%20regarding%20the%20proposed%20draft%20legislation%20at%20a%20more%20mature%20stage%20of%20its%20formulation'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-tells-centre-to-expedite-passage-of-controversial-broadcasting-services-bill%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22End%20of%20Kohli%20vs%20Anderson%20era%3A%20Fans%20react%20t