3EEvery%20Sunday%20at%206%20pm%2C%20the%20entire%20neighbourhood%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20some%20elderly%20gentlemen%2C%20would%20land%20up%20religiously%20at%20No.%202%2C%20Pratap%20Park.%20As%20the%20signature%20tune%20of%20Doordarshan%20filtered%20out%20onto%20the%20lanes%2C%20all%20the%20children%20would%20scurry%20down%20the%20streets%2C%20followed%20by%20their%20mothers%2C%20brothers%2C%20sisters%2C%20and%2C%20in%20my%20case%2C%20aunts%20and%20cousins%20too%2C%20to%20find%20the%20best%20seat%20in%20the%20house.%20The%20corridor%20outside%20their%20living%20room%2C%20a%20sea%20of%20footwear.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInside%2C%20the%20room%20would%20fill%20with%20anticipatory%20chatter%2C%20while%20the%20movie%20of%20the%20week%20was%20announced%20by%20probably%20the%20most%20well%20known%20face%20in%20the%20valley%2C%20a%20woman%20called%20Naseem%20Khan.%20The%20opening%20credits%20would%20be%20read%20aloud%20by%20all%20those%20who%20could.%20But%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20film%20started%2C%20the%20audience%20would%20be%20unable%20to%20take%20our%20eyes%20off%20the%20black%20and%20white%20images%20%E2%80%93%20each%20transported%20into%20our%20own%20dream%20world.%20Copious%20amounts%20of%20tears%2C%20hearty%20laughs%20at%20all%20the%20funny%20lines%2C%20and%20the%20rush%20of%20adrenaline%20as%20the%20bad%20guys%20got%20their%20due%20from%20the%20honest%2C%20upright%20hero%20%E2%80%93%20that%20was%20us.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20films%20screened%20on%20state-run%20television%20from%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%20were%20almost%20invariably%20about%20the%20protagonist%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20against%20poverty%2C%20and%20the%20effect%20it%20had%20on%20his%20relationships%20with%20his%20family%20or%20the%20love%20of%20his%20life.%20Inevitably%2C%20the%20hero%20triumphed%20against%20all%20odds.%20He%20did%20this%20by%20sticking%20to%20his%20principles%20to%20overcome%20the%20zamindar%20or%20the%20money%20lender%20or%20the%20factory%20owner.%20More%20often%20than%20not%2C%20the%20villains%20belonged%20to%20the%20rich%20upper%20class%2C%20whereas%20the%20hero%20was%20from%20a%20rural%2C%20lower-middle%2C%20or%20working%20class.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20were%20the%20stories%20from%20the%20glory%20days%20of%20Nehruvian%20socialism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201976%2C%20my%20father%20bought%20our%20first%20TV%20set%2C%20a%20Telerad%20that%20came%20with%20its%20own%20wooden%20cabinet.%20The%20neighbourhood%20split%20into%20two%20audiences.%20If%20I%20remember%20correctly%2C%20nobody%20ever%20asked%20my%20parents%20either%20if%20it%20was%20alright%20to%20barge%20in%20and%20watch%20the%20weekly%20film%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EChitrahaar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20show%20which%20featured%20film%20songs.%20And%20yet%2C%20they%20did%20barge%20in.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quarters%20and%20apartment%20blocks%20on%20Residency%20Road%20housed%20mainly%20journalists%20and%20some%20bureaucrats.%20Some%20of%20these%20people%20were%20non-Kashmiris%20and%20this%20contributed%20to%20making%20this%20a%20vibrant%20place.%20We%20were%20exposed%20to%20a%20bigger%20culture%20of%20news%20and%20politics%20at%20a%20very%20young%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20State%20Motor%20Garages%20was%20located%20here%20and%20housed%20all%20the%20government%20cars%20meant%20for%20VIPs%2C%20state%20officials%20and%20sundry%20dignitaries%2C%20At%20times%2C%20it%20became%20our%20playground.%20There%20were%20old%20open-top%20Cadillacs%20and%20Chevrolet%20Impalas%20and%20even%20a%20Volkswagen%20van%20that%20had%20a%20bed%20and%20a%20kitchenette%20inside.%20On%20quiet%20weekends%2C%20some%20of%20us%20would%20play%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echor%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E-police%2C%20enacting%20mock%20car%20chases%20and%20shootouts%20or%20digging%20the%20dirt%20for%20treasure%20behind%20the%20staff%20quarters.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%20we%20came%20up%20with%20glass%20bottoms%20of%20alcohol%20bottles%20as%20booty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20in%20this%20very%20neighbourhood%20that%20I%20got%20cast%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20a%20tele%20film%20for%20Doordarshan%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EEk%20Kahani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20I%20was%20four%20years%20old.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0Our%20home%20became%20a%20film%20set%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20days.%20All%20my%20scenes%20were%20shot%20there.%20I%20remember%20crying%20before%20every%20shot%20and%20it%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20cajoling%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20crew%20to%20calm%20me%20down%20with%20sweets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubconsciously%20the%20acting%20bug%20must%20have%20bitten%20me%20as%20lines%20between%20films%20and%20life%20blurred%20often%2C%20such%20as%20when%20I%20told%20off%20a%20relative%20who%20called%20me%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMaaji%20gobur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98mama%E2%80%99s%20boy%E2%80%99%20with%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAap%20ko%20kya%20pata%20Ma%20ka%20pyar%20kya%20hota%20hai%2C%20mamta%20kya%20hoti%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubconsciously%20the%20acting%20bug%20must%20have%20bitten%20me%20as%20lines%20between%20films%20and%20life%20blurred%20often%2C%20such%20as%20when%20I%20told%20off%20a%20relative%20who%20called%20me%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMaaji%20gobur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98mama%E2%80%99s%20boy%E2%80%99%20with%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAap%20ko%20kya%20pata%20Ma%20ka%20pyar%20kya%20hota%20hai%2C%20mamta%20kya%20hoti%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOr%20when%20a%20frustrated%20policeman%2C%20during%20the%20agitation%20in%20the%20summer%20of%201985%20ag