dations-1235906219%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22PM%20Modi%20surprises%20MPs%20with%20unexpected%20lunch%20at%20Parliament%20canteen%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707504242000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-02%2F10%2Ffull%2F1707503721-4555.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-surprises-mps-with-unexpected-lunch-at-parliament-canteen-124021000006_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20drill%20began%20a%20little%20earlier%20in%20the%20day%20when%20officials%20from%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20Office%20contacted%20the%20MPs%2C%20some%20of%20them%20first-time%20members%2C%20without%20giving%20away%20the%20details%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-surprises-mps-with-unexpected-lunch-at-parliament-canteen-124021000006_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-surprises-mps-with-unexpected-lunch-at-parliament-canteen-124021000006_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-surprises-mps-with-unexpected-lunch-at-parliament-canteen-124021000006_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BSonia%20Gandhi%20Acted%20As%20Super%20PM%26quot%3B%3A%20Finance%20Minister%20On%20%26quot%3BRudderless%26quot%3B%20UPA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMounting%20an%20all-out%20offensive%20against%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20UPA%20government%2C%20Finance%20Minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20the%20previous%20regime%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Brudderless%20and%20leaderless%26quot%3B%20one%20and%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20acted%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BSuper%20Prime%20Minister%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20reply%20to%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20white%20paper%20-%20comparing%20the%20economy%20under%20the%20Congress-led%20UPA%20from%202004%20to%202014%20and%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20since%20then%20-%C2%A0%20Ms%20Sitharaman%20also%20tore%20into%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20over%20the%202013%20incident%20when%20he%20'tore%20up'%20an%20ordinance%20proposed%20by%20the%20Manmohan%20Singh%20government.%20The%20finance%20minister%20dubbed%20him%20arrogant%20and%20called%20his%20act%20an%20insult%20of%20%26quot%3Bhis%20own%20Prime%20Minister%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20speaking%20on%20the%20scams%20that%20took%20place%20under%20the%20UPA%20government%20and%20stating%20that%20her%20government%20pulled%20out%20the%20Indian%20economy%20from%20the%20'Fragile%20Five'%20category%2C%20the%20finance%20minister%20said%20the%20genesis%20of%20the%20problems%20and%20mismanagement%20during%20the%20previous%20government's%20rule%20lay%20in%20the%20leadership%20issue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20in%20Hindi%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLeadership%20was%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20problem.%20The%20rudderless%2C%20leaderless%20leadership%20was%20the%20focal%20point%20of%20the%20UPA's%20mismanagement%2C%20its%20%3Cem%3Eghotala-%3C%2Fem%3Edriven%C2%A0(scam-driven)%2010%20years.%20Mrs%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20was%20the%20Super%20Prime%20Minister%20as%20the%20chairperson%20of%20the%20National%20Advisory%20Council%20(NAC)%20-%20an%20extra-constitutional%20and%20unaccountable%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Sitharaman%20alleged%20that%20there%20was%20pressure%20on%20governance%20because%20Mrs%20Gandhi%20got%20extra-constitutional%20authority%20as%20the%20chairperson%20of%20the%20NAC%2C%20which%20was%20set%20up%20as%20an%20advisory%20board%20for%20the%20prime%20minister.%20She%20claimed%20that%20710%20files%20were%20sent%20to%20the%20NAC%20for%20%26quot%3Bpermission%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20government.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20unaccountable%2C%20unanswerable%20power...%20why%20were%20710%20files%20sent%20to%20the%20NAC%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20asked.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20on%20the%20opposition%20over%20its%20repeated%20allegations%20that%20the%20government%20does%20not%20respect%20institutions%2C%20the%20finance%20minister%20brought%20up%20the%202013%20incident%20involving%20Rahul%20Gandhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrime%20Minister%20Manmohan%20Singh%20was%20abroad.%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20tore%20up%20an%20ordinance%20and%20threw%20it%20at%20a%20press%20conference.%20Isn't%20that%20insulting%20his%20own%20prime%20minister%3F%20%C2%A0He%20was%20arrogant...%20did%20not%20care%20for%20his%20own%20prime%20minister.%20They%20now%20shout%20about%20institutions%20and%20lecture%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20thundered.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2013%20Press%20Conference%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20ruled%20in%202013%20that%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20convicted%20with%20a%20minimum%20two-year%20sentence%20would%20be%20immediately%20disqualified%20and%20would%20not%20get%20three%20months%20to%20appeal%2C%20like%20they%20did%20until%20then%2C%20the%20Manmohan%20Singh%20government%20had%20proposed%20an%20ordinance%20to%20overturn%20the%20judgment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Gandhi%20had%20termed%20the%20ordinance%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20nonsense%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20at%20a%20press%20conference%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20personally%20think%20what%20the%20government%20is%20doing%20on%20the%20ordinance%20is%20wrong.%20It%20was%20a%20political%20decision%2C%20every%20party%20does%20it%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20time%20to%20stop%20this%20nonsense...%20If%20we%20actually%20want%20to%20stop%20corruption%20then%20we%20cannot%20make%20these%20compromises.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20said%20the%20ordinance%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Btorn%20and%20thrown%20out%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20proceeded%20to%20tear%20a%20piece%20of%20paper%20in%20front%20of%20the%20cameras.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Granary%20of%