x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-3-1707479405-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341329%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETaking%20out%20the%20stigmas%20from%20the%20flower%20is%20a%20manual%20time-consuming%20process%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Vaibhav%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aim%20is%20to%20mimic%20the%20climes%20of%20the%20Valley%2C%20as%20the%20seeds%20only%20flower%20at%20a%20specific%20temperature.%20Elaborating%20on%20how%20they%20managed%20to%20achieve%20this%2C%20Vaibhav%20says%20%E2%80%9CThe%20temperature%20in%20the%20room%20has%20to%20be%20decreased%20gradually%20just%20as%20if%20winter%20is%20coming%20to%20Kashmir.%20We%E2%80%99re%20essentially%20trying%20to%20make%20the%20seeds%20feel%20at%20home.%20So%2C%20we%20start%20at%2025%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20gradually%20drop%20the%20temperature%20to%20five%20degrees%20through%20the%20next%20four%20months%20until%20harvest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStep%204%3A%20Pluck%20the%20flowers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20purple%20bloom%20conveys%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F276908%2Fdehradun-gardener-flower-plants-how-to-garden-youtube%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20harvest%20is%20ready%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Each%20flower%20comprises%20petals%2C%20the%20stamen%20and%20the%20stigma.%20%E2%80%9CEach%20of%20these%20parts%20has%20a%20different%20use.%20The%20petals%20are%20used%20in%20the%20cosmetic%20industry%2C%20the%20yellow%20stamen%20is%20used%20in%20the%20textile%20industry%20for%20dyeing%2C%20and%20the%20stigma%20is%20the%20red%20saffron.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStep%205%3A%20Place%20the%20seeds%20back%20into%20the%20soil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20flowers%20have%20been%20plucked%20out%2C%20all%20the%20seeds%20are%20placed%20back%20into%20the%20soil%20so%20they%20can%20flower%20again%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Vaibhav%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20cycle%20that%20began%20on%2015%20August%20was%20completed%20on%201%20November%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEnsure%20that%20you%20water%20the%20seeds%20every%207%20to%2010%20days%2C%20and%20not%20exceed%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20informs.%20Once%20it%E2%80%99s%20August%2C%20the%20flowers%20will%20be%20harvested%20again.%20%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20you%20see%2C%20each%20bulb%20has%20a%20lifetime%20of%20a%20decade%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F17686%2F5-secrets-to-the-most-amazing-terrace-garden-from-expert-viswanath-kadur%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20saffron%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20one-time%20investment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20history%20loves%20this%20%E2%80%98red%20gold%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20is%20one%20spice%20that%20is%20history%E2%80%99s%20favourite%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20saffron.%20Legends%20tell%20of%20how%20Cleopatra%20bathed%20with%20it%20and%20Alexander%20the%20Great%20used%20it%20to%20heal%20battle%20wounds.%20Price%20is%20no%20bar%20it%20seems%20as%20some%20traders%20in%20Kashmir%20get%20a%20handsome%20Rs%202%20lakh%20per%20kg%20according%20to%20an%20article%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20sheds%20light%20on%20how%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20expensive%20spice%E2%80%9D%20is%20not%20every%20country%E2%80%99s%20cup%20of%20tea.%20Iran%20produces%2095%20percent%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20saffron%20and%20Kashmir%20a%20great%20margin%20too.%20The%20spice%E2%80%99s%20demand%20for%20a%20certain%20climate%20means%20not%20every%20country%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F332547%2Fsooraj-purushothaman-organic-farmer-kerala-gardening-growing-vegetables%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efavourable%20for%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20it%20takes%20one%20lakh%20flowers%20to%20produce%20one%20kg%20of%20saffron%20(and%20the%20entire%20process%20must%20be%20done%20by%20hand)%20adds%20to%20its%20expense.%20And%20farmers%20in%20Kashmir%20have%20mastered%20the%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-4-1707479491.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Once%20the%20flowers%20have%20been%20plucked%20the%20seeds%20are%20put%20into%20the%20soil%20once%20more%20for%20the%20next%20harvest%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-4-1707479491.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-4-1707479491-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-4-1707479491-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-4-1707479491-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-4-1707479491-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341330%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EOnce%20the%20flowers%20have%20been%20plucked%20the%20seeds%20are%20put%20into%20the%20soil%20once%20more%20for%20the%20next%20harvest%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Vaibhav%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-5-1707479616.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aastha%20and%20Vaibhav%20Patel%20have%20started%20growing%20saffron%20in%20their%20Vadodara%20home%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-5-1707479616.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-5-1707479616-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-5-1707479616-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-5-1707479616-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-5-1707479616-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341331%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAastha%20and%20Vaibhav%20Patel%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Vaibhav%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20said%20that%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%205%2C707%20hectares%20of%20land%20under%20saffron%20cultivation%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20more%20than%2090%20percent%20is%20in%20the%20Pampore%20tehsil%20of%20Pulwama%20district%20in%20South%20Kashmir.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20Valley%20rejoiced%20as%20the%20GI%20tag%20was%20given%20to%20Kashmiri%20saffron%20making%20it%20illegal%20for%20someone%20outside%20the%20valley%20to%20make%20and%20sell%20a%20similar%20product%20under%20the%20%E2%80%98Kashmiri%20saffron%E2%80%99%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20saffron%20grown%20in%20the%20Valley%20is%20of%20three%20types%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%98Lachha%20Saffron%E2%80%99%20is%20the%20variety%20where%20stigmas%20just%20separated%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F329424%2Fludhiana-woman-grows-200-plants-in-terrace-garden-watch-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20flowers%20are%20dried%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20further%20processing%3B%20%E2%80%98Mongra%20Saffron%E2%80%99%20is%20the%20variety%20where%20stigmas%20are%20detached%20from%20the%20flower%2C%20dried%20in%20the%20sun%2C%20and%20processed%20traditionally%3B%20and%20%E2%80%98Guchhi%20Saffron%E2%80%99%20which%20also%20does%20not%20involve%20the%20stigmas%20being%20processed.%20Instead%2C%20they%20are%20dried%20and%20joined%20in%20a%20bundle%20tied%20with%20a%20cloth%20thread.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20that%20the%20Patels%20are%20growing%20is%20the%20second%20variety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20first%20harvest%20was%20an%20experiment%2C%E2%80%9D%20Vaibhav%20emphasises.%20But%20lucrative%20all%20the%20same.%20Each%20gram%20of%20the%20red%20threads%20fetched%20the%20couple%20Rs%20700.%20As%20for%20the%20road%20ahead%2C%20they%20are%20confident%20they%20can%20expand%20sales%20implementing%20the%20learnings%20of%20the%20previous%20harvest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707485452000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIMG_0318_11zon-1707478888.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D341322%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22How%20to%20grow%20saffron%20at%20home%3F%20Vaibhav%20Patel%20and%20Aastha%20Maheshwari%20Patel%20have%20transformed%20their%20Vadodara%20home%20into%20a%20Kashmiri%20saffron%20haven%2C%20defying%20geographical%20norms.%20They%20share%20insights%20into%20the%20intricate%20process%20of%20growing%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20expensive%20spice%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Numbers%20Don't%20Lie%3A%20Public%20Debt%20Reduced%20in%20the%20UPA%20Era%2C%20Shot%20Up%20Under%20the%20Modi%20Govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F07131838%2Fmodi-sitha.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EUnion%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20released%20a%20%E2%80%9CWhite%20Paper%20on%20the%20Indian%20Economy%E2%80%9D%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%208%2C%20which%20purportedly%20seeks%20to%20%E2%80%9Cgenerate%20a%20wider%2C%20more%20informed%20debate%20on%20the%20paramountcy%20of%20national%20interest%20and%20fiscal%20responsibility%20in%20matters%20of%20governance%20over%20political%20expediency%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20Paper%20criticises%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmismanagement%20and%20short-sighted%20handling%20of%20the%20public%20finances%20during%20FY04-FY14%E2%80%9D%2C%20i.e.%20under%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20(UPA)%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20official%20data%20shows%20that%20when%20the%20UPA-I%20government%20took%20charge%20in%202004%2C%20the%20gross%20debt%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20was%20over%2067%25%20of%20GDP%20and%20the%20gross%20debt%20of%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20together%20(general%20government)%20was%20almost%2085%25%20of%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20UPA%20era%20ended%20in%202014%2C%20gross%20central%20government%20debt%20had%20come%20down%20to%20below%2053%25%20of%20GDP%20and%20general%20government%20debt%20to%20below%2067%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2010%20years%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20central%20government%20debt%20has%20climbed%20up%20to%2058%25%20of%20GDP%20in%20FY24%20and%20general%20government%20debt%20to%2082%25%20of%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublic%20Debt%2FGDP%20ratio%20declined%20during%20the%20UPA%20era%20because%20of%20two%20reasons%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20GDP%20grew%20at%20a%20rate%20much%20faster%20than%20the%20previous%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20Growth%20was%20driven%20by%20private%20investment%2C%20consumption%2C%20and%20exports%20allowing%20the%20government%20to%20maintain%20moderate%20fiscal%20deficits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067